Linux is a operating system.
The Linux operating system comprises several different pieces:
1. Bootloader
2. Kernel
3. Init System
4. Daemons
5. Graphical Server
6. Desktop Environment etc.
Linux has a number of different versions to suit any type of user.
Such as: Linux Mint, Manjaro, Debian, Ubuntu, Antergos, Fedora, Kali etc.
